CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 26, 1960, pg. 1 reads: "For Strong Civil Rights - More than 300 Chatham College students have endorsed a strong stand for civil rights for all. Some of them are shown with Albert J. Ossman Jr., assistant professor of political science and economics.  They are (left to right): Barbara Paull, Latrobe; Ann Smith, Camp Hill; Brenda Jones, Pittsburgh, and Glorianne Hubert, New York, who sent a protest letter to the United States Senate. (See letter on Page 16, Sec. 2) - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Chatham College students from left: Barbara Paull, Ann Smith, Albert J. Ossman Jr., assistant professor;  Brenda Jones, and Glorianne Hubert, gathered in interior, another version
